==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mastabah
<hw>Mas"ta*bah</hw> }</mhw>. <ety>[Ar. <ets>ma⟦cced⟧tabah</ets> a large
stone bench.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In Muslim countries, a fixed seat,
common in dwellings and in public places.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Egyptology)</fld> <def>A type of tomb, of the time
of the Memphite dynasties, comprising an oblong structure with sloping
sides (sometimes containing a decorated chamber, sometimes of solid
masonry), and connected with a mummy chamber in the rock
beneath.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mastax</ent>⟦br⟧
